<h2>6. Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>
<p><strong>Q1: Can I recover deleted downloads on Mac?</strong><br />A: Yes, via <strong>Trash</strong> before emptying, or using <strong>Time Machine backup</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Q2: Does deleting downloads improve Mac speed?</strong><br />A: Yes, especially if your Downloads folder contains GBs of files.</p>
<p><strong>Q3: Can I automate deletion of downloads?</strong><br />A: Yes, using <strong>Automator workflows</strong> or <strong>cron jobs</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Q4: Is it safe to use Terminal commands?</strong><br />A: Only if you type commands carefully. <code>rm -rf</code> can permanently erase important data.</p>
<p><strong>Q5: Do browser downloads stay if I delete files from Finder?</strong><br />A: The download record in Chrome or Safari will remain, but the file will be gone.</p>
